# Adapted from https://github.com/eyereasoner/eye/blob/master/reasoning/deep-taxonomy/
# (test-rules.n3's backward subClassOf rule, unmodified) combined with a
# heavily truncated slice of test-dl.ttl + test-facts.ttl: upstream's
# benchmark chains :N0 all the way through :N10000 down to :A2 (a
# 10000-level-deep, ~30000-triple scalability stress test); this keeps only
# a 3-level chain (:N0 -> :N1 -> :N2 -> :A2) to exercise the same
# rdfs:subClassOf backward-chaining transitivity rule as a fast conformance
# check rather than a scale benchmark.
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>.
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>.
@prefix : <http://eulersharp.sourceforge.net/2009/12dtb/test#>.

:TestVariable rdf:type :N0.

:N0 rdfs:subClassOf :N1.
:N1 rdfs:subClassOf :N2.
:N2 rdfs:subClassOf :A2.

{?X a ?D} <= {?C rdfs:subClassOf ?D. ?X a ?C}.
